<div class='allCommunityAnswers'>
<div class='communityAnswer'>
<div class='communityAnswerBody'>
<div class='answererUserIcon'>
<a class="leftAlignedImage userPhoto" href="/user/show/40140873-erin"><img alt="" src="https://s.gr-assets.com/assets/nophoto/user/f_100x100-6433b08cbe793211f55e184d39e84c4d.png" /></a>
</div>
<div class='communityAnswerTextContainer'>
<span class='communityAnswererName'>
<a href="/user/show/40140873-erin">Erin</a>
</span>
<span class='communityAnswerText'>
<span class="expandableContainer"><span class="truncatedContent">What type of being other than an egomaniacal sadist would create a world and allow unbearable suffering among children and innocents while demanding w<a class="jsShow showAction" href="#">…more</a></span><span class="fullContent">What type of being other than an egomaniacal sadist would create a world and allow unbearable suffering among children and innocents while demanding worship? Using a separate being as a sacrifice to earn "paradise" that is supposedly more worship of the being only adds to the farce. Considering suffering a "spectator sport" is the most polite way to describe the Christian god and many of its followers.<a class="jsHide hideAction" href="#">(less)</a></span></span>
</span>
</div>
