        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer1709923747" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer7040859626306773218">What a weird, strange, engrossing book this is. It defies description. Beautifully written and with ideas that will have you thinking for days. Like the idea that hell is a place without Hope or that the devil prays for forgiveness. But the story itself grabs you. Is this young boy truly the devil? <br/><br/>I love that the author chooses 1984 as the year the novel takes place. The book constantly harkens back to Orwell’s novel with its groupthink and ideas of “truth”. But it&apos;s also a book that fits with </span>
  <span id="freeText7040859626306773218" style="display:none">What a weird, strange, engrossing book this is. It defies description. Beautifully written and with ideas that will have you thinking for days. Like the idea that hell is a place without Hope or that the devil prays for forgiveness. But the story itself grabs you. Is this young boy truly the devil? <br /><br />I love that the author chooses 1984 as the year the novel takes place. The book constantly harkens back to Orwell’s novel with its groupthink and ideas of “truth”. But it's also a book that fits with the current times and the hate currently enveloping the country. <br /><br />It's not a story that ends well. If anything, the book shows that hell is often right here on earth. But despite the sadness this book evokes, I heartily recommend it. <br /><br /></span>
  <a data-text-id="7040859626306773218" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

